  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age between 20 and 65 years

          -  Complex anal fistula defined as

               -  anterior fistulas in women

               -  branched fistulas

               -  fistulas in patients with anal incontinence

               -  fistulas traversing more than 30% of the anal sphincter and therefore unsuitable
                  for simple division.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Crohn's disease in the rectum

          -  Previous LIFT surgery on same side

          -  Patient already treated with seton &gt; 3 weeks

          -  Not able or willing to sign informed consent
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
